main event: Two objects with blue-green lights were observed maneuvering in the sky near the witness, who was located approximately 100 yards away from the objects.
interesting points: The objects approached to about 90 degrees from the witness's position, then appeared to make a steep climb and took off at high speed, disappearing from view.
The sighting lasted for approximately 1 minute.
The report includes a conclusion that the object remains unidentified after a thorough investigation, with no evidence of any conventional aircraft or other man-made object in the area at the time.
The sighting occurred on September 9, 1960 at around 2330 GCT (Grenwich Mean Time).
The weather conditions at the time were clear sky and bright moonlight.
